      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "No. An URL is just a special case of an URI. A file URI starts with &quot;file://&quot; and then lists the host (generally omitted), followed by &quot;/&quot; and the path &quot;foo/bar&quot; (generally meant to be read as an absolute path). Thus &quot;file:///foo/var&quot;. An URI that looks like &quot;file:/foo/bar&quot; is incorrect. See also: <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File_URI_scheme\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">file URI scheme</a>"
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 1175385,
        "reputation" : 23793,
